--------------------------------------------------------------------

Need a unified scheme in handling messages in SM:

When LC client sends a message/request to SM, if SM can fulfill the request
without contacting the SUP, SM will simply call ipc_send_rpc_reply_blocked()
to the client.  After that SM will free the request message buffer.

If SM needs to forward the request to SUP, it will reuse its buffer for
the forward message.  No clean up should be done yet.
When response from SUP is received, SM will forward the result to
LC client using ipc_send_rpc_reply_blocked() to the client.
